South African Gold Production Rose 6.4% in Quarter, Chamber of Mines Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-09-06T12:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/south-african-gold-production-rose-6-4-in-quarter-chamber-of-mines-says.html
South African gold production rose
6.4 percent in the second quarter compared with the previous
three months, the Chamber of Mines of  South Africa  said.  Output climbed to 1.53 million ounces during the three
months to June 30 from 1.44 million ounces in the first quarter,
the industry group said in an e-mailed statement today.  Compared with a year earlier, production of the precious
metal declined 1.8 percent, according to the statement.  The chamber represents producers including  AngloGold
Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) ,  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  and Harmony Gold Mining Ltd.  South Africa was the worldâ€™s fifth largest gold producer
last year, trailing  China , Australia, the U.S. and Russia,
according to London-based research company GFMS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
